Sometimes the midwife must take the knife and perform the Caesarean operation, as witness Caesar, the glory of the Roman tace, and Manlius; yea and also [Scipio] the destroyer of the Libyan name. Even in the realm of Gods the art of the midwife is not unknown. Witness Latona‘s throes, and Jupiter's pangs at Pallas' birth. His midwife was Mul- ciber (Vulcan) with his skull-cleaving hatchet. What would Jove have given for the old dame now languishing in prison? She would have been a godsend, a welcome help, needing no harsh weapon to give relief.
